gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Suns 109, Trail Blazers 88
gameRecap.excerpt: The Suns defeated the Trail Blazers, 109-88. Bradley Beal recorded a team-high 21 points, along with four rebounds for the Suns, while Jusuf Nurkic added 18 points (6-8 FG), seven rebounds, and five assists in the victory. Scoot Henderson tallied 17 points and six assists for the Trail Blazers in the losing effort. The Suns are on a four game winning streak as they improve to 18-15 on the season, while the Trail Blazers fall to 9-23.
